The paper deals with the problem of guarding a polygon, which is a classic problem in computational geometry and falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the approximation algorithms, which involves the analysis of algorithms and approximation theory, making it relevant to categories such as data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and complexity theory (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper discusses the visibility structures of simple polygons, which is related to the graph theory (cs.GT).
